{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17511031","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17511031"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T12:36:40+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T12:36:40+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11691"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"11691","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/11691"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.07,0.49,0.07,0.29,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4306"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80647"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4306","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4306"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11691"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65943"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"13"},{"type":"tags","id":"23"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"147"},{"type":"tags","id":"449"},{"type":"tags","id":"3514"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4965"},{"type":"tags","id":"4980"},{"type":"tags","id":"5967"},{"type":"tags","id":"9644"},{"type":"tags","id":"11020"},{"type":"tags","id":"11061"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11634"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"5854"},{"type":"contributions","id":"6208"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26966"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43259"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44282"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80647","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80647"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 35-year-old woman who is 32 weeks pregnant with twins receives treatment for iron deficiency anaemia. At the beginning of her pregnancy, her ferritin level was 2 \u00b5g/L without anemia. She was started on oral iron supplementation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOne week ago, her iron studies showed a ferritin level of 15\u00b5g/L. She reports constipation from the iron supplements and would like to consider an iron infusion.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EShe also has asthma and throughout this pregnancy has developed gestational diabetes and pre-eclampsia.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following factors would increase the patient\u0027s risk of an adverse reaction to the iron infusion?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Late stage pregnancy","Asthma","Gestational Diabetes","Pre-eclampsia","Twin pregnancy"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe main adverse effect of concern with an iron infusion is a hypersensitivity anaphylactic reaction due to a complement activated allergy to the particles in the iron infusion. Major risk factors that increase the likelihood of a hypersensitivity reaction include: severe atopy including \u003Cstrong\u003Easthma\u003C/strong\u003E and eczema; history of drug or food allergies and systemic inflammatory diseases or chronic infection.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELate stage pregnancy:\u003C/strong\u003E Iron infusions are contraindicated in early stage pregnancy but are recommended from the 2nd trimester onwards as the preferred method of rebuilding iron stores.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGestational diabetes, pre-eclampsia and twin pregnancy:\u003C/strong\u003E There is no association between these conditions and an iron infusion.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Hypersensitivity reactions are the most concerning adverse effect of iron infusions.","History of severe atopy increases the risk of an iron infusion induced hypersensitivity reaction."],"references":["Rampton D, Folkersen J, Fishbane S, Hedenus M, Howaldt S, Locatelli F, Patni S, Szebeni J, Weiss G. Hypersensitivity reactions to intravenous iron: guidance for risk minimization and management. Haematologica. 2014 Nov;99(11):1671-6. doi: 10.3324/haematol.2014.111492. PMID: 25420283; PMCID: PMC4222472. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25420283/","Australian Medicines Handbook [Internet]. Adelaide: AMH; c2020. Iron [cited 2022, May 16] Available from: https://amhonline.amh.net.au/","G\u00f3mez-Ram\u00edrez S, Shander A, Spahn DR, Auerbach M, Liumbruno GM, Vaglio S, Mu\u00f1oz M. Prevention and management of acute reactions to intravenous iron in surgical patients. Blood Transfus. 2019 Mar;17(2):137-145. doi: 10.2450/2018.0156-18. Epub 2018 Oct 16. PMID: 30418128; PMCID: PMC6476739. Available from: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC6476739/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65943"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11691"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65943","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65943"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-22T06:48:44+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-22T06:49:49+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4306"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80647"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"13","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/13"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\ude78","name":"Haematology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:44+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"23","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/23"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd30","name":"Obstetrics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"po